d the services we provide. With the young carer and their parents permission, you can then refer them to our service using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/8\" target=\"_blank\">Annual Report for 2009/10 </a>provides information about our charity and what we achieved over the 2009/10 annual period.</p>\r\n','2010-05-21 16:08:01','2010-10-22 14:12:28','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-05-21 15:08:00',1,52,0),(7,2,'Summer Programme 2010','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras eu lorem est, nec lacinia nunc. Maecenas et sem vel quam ullamcorper pharetra. Vivamus orci diam, venenatis tincidunt ultrices eu, condimentum a odio. Sed in ipsum sem. In posuere, velit sed facilisis vulputate, urna risus posuere purus, eu rhoncus erat purus a nibh. Pellentesque at tortor a tortor sagittis bibendum. Phasellus sapien velit, posuere eu dignissim ut, lobortis nec tortor. Fusce a eros quis arcu iaculis malesuada. Quisque venenatis dignissim enim id commodo. Fusce condimentum felis nec magna sodales quis imperdiet lorem fringilla. Sed luctus luctus diam sed fermentum. Donec tempus facilisis hendrerit. Nunc consequat lacinia arcu, eu ornare lectus consequat vel. Phasellus a tristique augue. Sed felis diam, egestas a tristique facilisis, ornare sollicitudin ante. Nam ac viverra ipsum. Fusce vitae mi in diam pharetra tincidunt. Proin a lacus urna. ','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	School holidays can be a lonely and challenging time for young people who have caring responsibilities. To support our project members during the summer holidays, we have an action-packed programme of activities and workshops on offer, including:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Outdoor activity residentials in the Peak District</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A performance / digital animation / film project</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A health and well-being workshop</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Swimming</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Design workshops</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Picnics at local parks</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		And much much more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have any other ideas for holiday activities, please get in touch.</p>\r\n','2010-05-21 16:15:09','2010-08-12 14:36:53','2010-08-31 22:00:00','2010-05-21 12:15:00',1,289,2),(8,2,'Our new website','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras eu lorem est, nec lacinia nunc. Maecenas et sem vel quam ullamcorper pharetra. Vivamus orci diam, venenatis tincidunt ultrices eu, condimentum a odio. Sed in ipsum sem. In posuere, velit sed facilisis vulputate, urna risus posuere purus, eu rhoncus erat purus a nibh. Pellentesque at tortor a tortor sagittis bibendum. Phasellus sapien velit, posuere eu dignissim ut, lobortis nec tortor. Fusce a eros quis arcu iaculis malesuada. Quisque venenatis dignissim enim id commodo. Fusce condimentum felis nec magna sodales quis imperdiet lorem fringilla. Sed luctus luctus diam sed fermentum. Donec tempus facilisis hendrerit. Nunc consequat lacinia arcu, eu ornare lectus consequat vel. Phasellus a tristique augue. Sed felis diam, egestas a tristique facilisis, ornare sollicitudin ante. Nam ac viverra ipsum. Fusce vitae mi in diam pharetra tincidunt. Proin a lacus urna. ','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Hot news! We&#39;ve launched our new website to coincide with Carers Week 2010. This is exciting for young people who take on a caring responsibility. Along with their families, they can find out where to get help and support, either from other people or organisations in Sheffield.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&#39;ve enjoyed an incredible journey in developing the website; some of the young people spent a sunny day having their photos taken by a professional photographer. Others joined in and had their say on what the website would look like, choosing the actual design and colours for the site. They&#39;ve also written what it&#39;s like to be a young carer and what SYC does!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The young people are looking forward to making the Young People&rsquo;s Portal active, fun cool and friendly for everyone; full of news, poems, puzzles and games.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now we&#39;re up and live, please don&rsquo;t waste time - tell everyone about our fantastic website! Please pass on our details.</p>\r\n','2010-05-21 16:16:40','2010-10-13 21:11:37','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-05-21 12:16:00',1,68,7),(10,1,'Our staff team',NULL,'<div class=\"team_photo\">\r\n	<h4>\r\n		<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141625_5.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=ca14607ab9158d7d\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px\" />Liz Church &ndash; Manager</h4>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Liz is responsible for the management SYC and its staff on behalf of the Management Committee. Liz also works closely with the charities funders and other agencies to ensure that good quality and extensive support is made available to young carers in Sheffield.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h4>\r\n	&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_3.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;s=4933fc4a084c7e8a\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px\" />Laura Selby &ndash; Development and Support Worker</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Laura is employed full time at SYC to work with, and provide information to a wide range of organisations in Sheffield to make them aware of the work of the charity and how they can support young carers. Laura also leads 2 of our activity groups for young carers, takes part in excursions and residentials and provides one to one support where this is needed.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_4.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;s=3f6b952affbc8894\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px\" />Helen Goldsby-West &ndash; Fundraising Officer</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Helen is employed part time at SYC to research and make grant applications to ensure that SYC has the necessary funds to support young carers needs in Sheffield. Helen also leads fundraising and publicity campaigns and supports those wishing to fundraise for the charity.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h4>\r\n	&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141623_2.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;s=6e48b63860d28bd3\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px\" />Denise Anderson &ndash; Administration, Finance and Support Worker</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Denise works full time to provide administration support to the SYC staff team, and ensure that the charity finances are properly managed. Denise also encourages new volunteers to support the charity and leads a regular activity group.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141622_1.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;s=da3430f07ad7b2db\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px\" />Steph Platt &ndash; Support Worker</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Steph works part time for SYC and leads a regular activity group to support young carers in South Sheffield.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our staff are also supported by a dedicated team of volunteers without whom the support we offer would not be possible.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2010-05-27 09:05:58','2010-06-23 09:05:47','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-05-27 08:05:00',1,NULL,1),(11,2,'Chris\'s Swim Results',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	As promised here is the update on Chris Lawrence&#39;s sponsored swim for SYC.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chris completed her 1 mile swim of the London Thames as part of the Great London Swim on 3rd July. She was thrilled to have been mistakenly grouped with the &#39;Elite Swimmers&#39; (having only taken up exercise 10 months ago!) and completed the swim in 1 hour and 17 minutes giving her a commendable 3109 placing out of 5000 participants.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chris became aware of the issues that many young carers face during her career as a teacher in the London area, and is keen to support the good work that we do here at SYC. She has raised a commendable &pound;500 to date and sponsorship is still coming in.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For further information in Chris and her swim as well as a video of the day please <a href=\"http://web.me.com/bronnick/MyGreatSwim/Welcome.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It isn&#39;t too late to sponsor&nbsp;Chris and you can still do so by going to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/ChrisSYCP\">www.justgiving.com/ChrisSYCP</a> or, if you would like to support us with your own fundraising idea please get in touch.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chris here at SYC we think you are amazing - thank you again!</p>\r\n','2010-06-01 19:18:51','2010-10-13 21:11:16','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-01 15:18:00',1,67,6),(12,9,'What it means to be a young carer',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	A young carer is someone aged under 21 who cares for a relative or friend who has physical or mental health issues, a disability or problems with drugs or alcohol.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Young carers provide help by doing things like chores, shopping, helping with hygiene (bathing, getting dressed), giving medication and looking after younger brothers and sisters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Being a young carer can affect you in many ways. You aren&rsquo;t able to go out much, or able to access the same opportunities as other young people. You might end up getting in trouble for missing school or being distracted.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes you might feel very scared and stressed about the person you are looking after in case they get worse or something happens when you are not with them.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A lot of people don&rsquo;t understand what it feels like to be a young carer. You might feel angry or have mood swings. Also, when you are caring so much for someone else you might not look after yourself very well, such as not eating, sleeping or getting enough exercise.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	But it can feel really special to be a young carer. You can feel proud of what you do and be happy to spend time with the people you love.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	And there are lots of places you can go for support and things you can do to help. There are lots of ideas on this site, and also in our young peoples area <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/young-carers-4-life\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">YC4L</span>.</a></p>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:22:05','2010-10-21 22:02:57','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 08:22:00',1,43,0),(13,8,'Is my child or relative a young carer?',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	A young carer is someone aged under 21 who cares for a relative who has physical or mental health issues, a disability or problems with drugs or alcohol.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	You may have someone a young person in your family who is providing substantial help to a family member by doing household chores (shopping, cooking, cleaning), looking after siblings, providing emotional support, helping with washing or dressing a parent or relative or providing other support. This young person is likely to be a young carer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For many families, especially single parent families with no relatives nearby and families where one parent works long hours, this seems like the only option to get by.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	SYC is here to help and support young people doing a caring role.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To find out more about SYC and our staff team please visit the <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/sections/1\">About Us</a> page.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:23:56','2010-06-10 14:25:05','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 08:23:00',0,44,0),(14,8,'How we support young carers',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Young Carers Groups</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We run regular young carers groups which give young carers a break from their caring responsibilities, and also provide support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These groups give young carers the chance to socialise, have fun and share experiences with other young people in the same situation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The groups are free and we either provide transport or pay bus fares so your child or relative can attend.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes the groups go on trips such as bowling, swimming or for a meal.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	One to One Support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	If a young carer would like to talk about something difficult that is happening, or how they are feeling, one of our staff can visit them to provide support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We can also provide a one to one visit if a young person is new to SYC and wants to know more about what we do and how we can help them and their family.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We will only accept referrals to support a young carer where they have given permission for information about them to be shared with us. We will also ask for parent/carer&rsquo;s permission for us to support the young carer wherever possible. It is the families choice whether or not to receive support from SYC.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:27:58','2010-06-10 14:18:43','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:27:58',0,40,0),(15,8,'How we can support you',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	As a parent or relative you may feel easier, and less concerned, by the support that we may be able to offer to the young carer, knowing they have a place to go and that they can meet and socialise with other young people with similar experiences.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition to supporting the young carer, we may be able to offer some wider support and advice to you and your family.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We can put you into contact with organisations who may be able to offer services and support to meet your needs, such as emotional and practical advice or support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are also currently trying to attract grants to employ a Family Worker whose role will be to work with the family as a whole. This worker will support the cared for family member to access services and support which reduce the caring responsibilities of the young person.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Useful links for parents and family members of young carers</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	We will be providing links to other useful sites very soon. In the meantime you may find it useful to <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/useful-links-for-young-carers-and-their-friends\">take a look at the links</a> we provide for young carers and their friends.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Keep in touch</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Visit our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to sign up for email news for young carers.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:29:02','2010-06-10 14:26:46','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:29:02',0,23,0),(16,4,'About young carers',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	About young carers</h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Young carers are children or young people who provide a substantial amount of care for someone at home, usually a relative or friend, who has a physical or mental illness, disability or substance misuse problem.</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Young carers take on practical and/or emotional caring responsibilities that would normally be expected of an adult.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	These children and young people are known as &lsquo;young carers&rsquo; and we support them by offering one to one support, group activities, respite breaksholidays and support with education, employment and training.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Children and young people who look after someone and are taking on substantive caring roles don&rsquo;t often know they are young carers because they have done it all their lives.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>&lsquo;In Sheffield there are at least 2,000 young carers under the age of 16&rsquo;</em> according to Sheffield First&#39;s Health and Well-being Partnership&#39;s &#39;Sheffield: a city where every carer matters - A joint strategy for transforming the lives of carers in Sheffield 2010 - 2013&#39;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition to the young person&rsquo;s primary caring role, families with a cared for adult may encounter additional problems linked to their illness which may include &ndash; becoming a single parent, low income or unemployment, debt, housing problems, substance or alcohol misuse, relationship difficulties, domestic violence, anxiety and isolation.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	The impact of caring on a young person&rsquo;s life</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition to the problems families may encounter where an adult is receiving care from a young person, young carers lives may be affected by their caring role in a number of ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Educationally &ndash; irregular attendance, poor timekeeping/punctuality, lack of concentration, difficulties in completing homework.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Restricted training and employment choices &ndash; lack of time for personal development, poor flexibility in work practices.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Emotionally &ndash; stress, worry, tiredness, depression, insecurity, anxiety.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Social isolation &ndash; lack of access to/time for social activities, bullying and isolation from peers.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physically &ndash; injuries, strain.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The issues above, and their combined impact on young carers often result in young carers being marginalised and socially excluded. This may then lead to low educational and career aspirations, unemployment or low paid employment, relationship difficulties, isolation, mental health problems, substance misuse and criminal behaviour.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:48:36','2010-06-16 14:26:10','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 08:48:00',1,22,1),(17,4,'Education',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Teachers are often our first point of contact for the identification and referral of young carers.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Young carers are not easy to identify as they may actively try to conceal their caring role from school staff and peers for fear of outside interference or bullying.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Recognising some of these key signs may help you to identify young carers within school:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Late for and miss days of school for no apparent reason</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Tired and withdrawn</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Difficulty joining into social and extra-curricular activities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Isolated or a victim of bullying....but in contrast they may be confident with adults</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Under-achievement, poor, late or incomplete homework/coursework</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Anxiety or concern for a relative</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Behavioural problems, expressing pent up frustration or stress</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physical problems such as strain or injury caused by aspects of their caring role</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The positive steps you can take to help:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Speak to the young person privately, explain the confidentiality rules that teachers work to in age appropriate language.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to establish the caring tasks they are performing and why, how their caring role is affecting them (are they missing out on opportunities, are they being bullied, are they tried or stressed), and how you might be able to help them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ask for the young person&rsquo;s permission to speak to their parent/s and try to explain the effects of the young person&rsquo;s caring role on their education and the additional support that may be available. Please try to remember here that few parents choose a caring role for their child &ndash; it is often the only option and they may feel very guilty.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Outline to parents and children their entitlement to an assessment of their needs from social services and how this may help them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Support the family in contacting us (Sheffield Young Carers) or other organisations and agencies if they choose. Use our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to do this.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about SYC and the services we provide. With the young carer and their parents permission, you can then refer them to our service using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to draw up a realistic action plan with the family which will allow the young carer to attend school and achieve educationally.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Use sources provided below by The Royal Princess Trust for Carers, or alternatively from <a href=\"http://www.teachernet.gov.uk/management/atoz/y/youngcarers/\" target=\"_blank\">The Department of Education</a>, which provide advice and guidance for teachers.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Consider appointing and training a designated member of staff with the responsibility of supporting young carers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Positive steps your school can take:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.carers.org/professionals/young-carers/articles/schools-action-list,3111,PR.html\">Schools action list</a></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Sources provided for Schools and Local Authorities by The Royal Princess Trust for Carers</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://static.carers.org/files/young-carers-guidance-for-schools-las-08-07-ok-3128.doc\">Young Carers: Guidance for Schools and Local Authorities (466 KB)</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://static.carers.org/files/prt-schools-guide-1-4025.pdf\">Doing the Right Thing Well in Schools: A Good Practice Guide for working with young carers in schools (200 KB)</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://professionals.carers.org/young-carers/articles/schools-resource-pack,6282,PR.html\" target=\"_blank\">Supporting Young Carers: A Resource Pack for Schools</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-02 09:58:09','2010-10-21 21:48:58','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 08:58:00',1,38,3),(18,9,'Who we are',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Sheffield Young Carers is a Charity set up in 1997 to give young people aged 8-21 in Sheffield who are caring for someone a break from what they do and support them with any difficulties they may be having.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our staff below are responsible for supporting young carers in a number of ways:</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141625_5.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=ca14607ab9158d7d\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px;\" />Liz Church- Manager</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Liz supports all staff to make sure they provide a good service to young carers. Her job is also to work with the organisations that fund us to keep ensure the service keeps going and make links with other agencies that could help young carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_3.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=4933fc4a084c7e8a\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px;\" /></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Laura Selby &ndash; Development and Support Worker</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Laura supports all our groups for young carers and leads on the group for young carers aged 16-21. She&nbsp;also provides one to one support for young carers when they need it. Laura&rsquo;s role is also to work with other organisations, such as schools, to tell them about young carers and how they can support young carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 19px; line-height: 28px;\"><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141623_2.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=6e48b63860d28bd3\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px;\" />Denise Anderson &ndash; Administration, Finance and Support Worker</span><br />\r\n	Denise does some of the office work at SYC, such as administration and the accounts. Denise also leads a regular group for young carers aged 13-16.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141622_1.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=da3430f07ad7b2db\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px;\" />Stephanie Platt &ndash; Support Worker<br />\r\n	<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">Stephanie works on a group for young carers aged 12-21 who want to have more of a say about young carers issues. </span></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_4.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=3f6b952affbc8894\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px;\" />Helen Goldsby West &ndash; Fundraiser</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Helen&#39;s main focus is researching and making applications for money to run Sheffield Young Carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information about these and our other staff please visit our <a href=\"../../sections/1\">About Us</a> page</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:01:44','2010-09-15 13:36:02','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:01:44',1,51,0),(19,9,'What we can do to help',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Young Carers Groups</h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We run regular young carers groups which give you a break from your caring, and also provide support.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	These groups give you the chance to socialise, have fun and share experiences with other young carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The groups are free and we either provide transport or pay your bus fare so you can attend.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes the groups go on trips such as bowling, swimming or for a meal.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	One to One Support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you need help and support due to something that is happening to you, or the way you are feeling, one of our staff can visit you to provide one to one support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We can also provide a one to one visit if you are new to SYC and want to know more about what we do and how we can help you.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Family Support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are currently trying to raise money through donations and grants to employ a Family Worker. This new worker will support cared for family members to access services and support which reduce the amount of caring for the young person.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:04:24','2010-06-17 14:11:02','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:04:24',1,19,0),(20,9,'What you can do if you think you are a young carer',NULL,'<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Get in touch with us using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Visit our young people&#39;s pages <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/young-carers-4-life\" target=\"_blank\">YC4L</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		See our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/pages/24\">Useful Links</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to talk to someone you trust about what is happening at home and how you feel</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to stay healthy by eating a balanced diet and exercising</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to relax by listening to music</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to write about your experiences and how you are feeling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:07:14','2010-10-21 22:05:20','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:07:14',1,28,0),(21,4,'Health and Adult Social Care',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Young carers often lack key information about health conditions of family member/s they are caring for, and may also experience health problems themselves as a result of their caring duties.</h5>\r\n<h2>\r\n	How to identify and help a young carer if you work with adults</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Whenever you work with a client who has a care need due to their disability, illness or a substance misuse problem, ask yourself who is looking after that person at home.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Some individuals care needs will be met by an adult carer or other professionals but, as the census has shown, in tens of thousands of cases, a child is the primary carer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To identify individuals supported by a young carer, ask clients the following questions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Who helps to care for you at home?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Do you have children?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		What effects do you feel that your help problem has on them?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		How much do they help out?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Do you feel that you need more support as a parent?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Do you think that your children need more support?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Once you have identified a young person with caring responsibilities, a young carer, you may be able to help them in the following ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Approach them in an age appropriate and sensitive way &ndash; don&rsquo;t assume that even those who outwardly appear mature and confident feel the same on the inside.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about how they feel &ndash; whilst young carers spend most of their time looking after someone at home, they may be the person who knows least about the health condition of the cared for person.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to encourage your client to explain their health condition to their children; they may need your support in doing so.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Give young carers the information they need to answer questions they may have which can include &ndash; can I catch it, will it happen to me too, what caused it, was it my fault, can I do anything to make them better, will they get worse or die, what should I do in an emergency?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Assess/consider the needs of the whole family; this is often the best way to establish and provide help for the young carer.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about SYC and the services we provide, with the young carer and their parents permission you can then refer them to our service using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:07:43','2010-10-24 16:46:49','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:07:00',1,291,4),(22,4,'Children\'s Services',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Children&rsquo;s services are usually well placed to indentify, support and refer young carers to SYC and other appropriate organisations/agencies. However, sometimes this is not easy as many young carers actively try to conceal their caring role for fear of outside interference in their families, fear of being taken into care or a perceived loyalty to their families. It is also worth remembering that most young people undertaking a caring role do not identify themselves as young carers.</h5>\r\n<h2>\r\n	How to identify and help a young carer</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Recognising some of these key signs may help you to identify young carers within children you work with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Late for and miss days of school or social activities (such as a youth club) for no apparent reason</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Tired and withdrawn</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Difficulty joining into social and extra-curricular activities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Isolated or a victim of bullying....but in contrast they may be confident with adults</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Under-achievement in school or socially</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Secretive and protective of their home life</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Anxiety or concern for a relative and a need to be in constant contact with someone at home</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Behavioural problems, expressing pent up frustration or stress</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physical problems such as strain or injury caused by aspects of their caring role</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Positive steps that you can take to help:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Approach them in an age appropriate and sensitive way &ndash; don&rsquo;t assume that even those who outwardly appear mature and confident feel the same on the inside.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about how they feel &ndash; whilst young carers spend most of their time looking after someone at home, they may be the person who knows least about the health condition of the cared for person.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to encourage the cared for person to explain their health condition to the young carer; they may need your support in doing so.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Give young carers the information they need to answer questions they may have which can include &ndash; can I catch it, will it happen to me too, what caused it, was it my fault, can I do anything to make them better, will they get worse or die, what should I do in an emergency?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Assess/consider the needs of the whole family; this is often the best way to establish and provide help for the young carer.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about SYC and the services we provide, with the young carer and their parents permission you can then refer them to our service using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:10:00','2010-10-24 16:48:10','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:10:00',1,144,5),(23,9,'How you can help a friend who is a young carer',NULL,'<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Get in touch with us using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Visit our young people&#39;s pages <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/young-carers-4-life\" target=\"_blank\">YC4L</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		See our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/pages/24\">Useful Links</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Be trustworthy &ndash; keep what is happening in your friends family a secret if they ask you to</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Be there for them, but back off when they are in a bad mood or want to be alone</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Understand that they can&rsquo;t always go out</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Listen to them when they&rsquo;re upset or explaining what is wrong with the person they care for</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Take them seriously and try to imagine how it feels</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Remember important dates &ndash; like when someone has died or when someone has to go to hospital</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Don&rsquo;t use them &ndash; young carers are very caring people!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:11:38','2010-10-21 22:06:12','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:11:38',1,24,0),(24,9,'Useful links',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Here&#39;s some external sources of information which you might like to look at to find other support:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To find out about different illnesses, read a young carers blog, find out what to do in an emergency and get loads of other support about being a young carer, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarers.net/\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you want to know about getting help at school or with your homework, or to find out who all the people are who work with your family, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarer.com/showPage.php?file=20098594936.htm\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To find out more about the illness that affects your family member and get information about being a young carer and the feelings you might have, <a href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/CarersDirect/young\">go to</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For loads of information about your own or your family&rsquo;s health issues, click <a href=\"http://www.childrenfirst.nhs.uk/\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To get information and support about your own feelings and mental health <a href=\"http://www.youngminds.org.uk\">check out</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you want to find about activities in your own area, <a href=\"http://www.asksid.net\">click</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you have a parent with cancer, you can get information and support <a href=\"http://www.riprap.org.uk\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If someone at home uses drugs and alcohol, there is a project called &lsquo;What About Me&rsquo; who run programmes to help. You can get more information by phoning Imogen Powell on 0114 275 5973.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you or someone at home is living with HIV/AIDS, there is a support and social group that meets every two weeks. To find out more, phone Evelyn Joseph on 0114 281 1352</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you have a brother or sister with a&nbsp; disability, &lsquo;Sibling Support&rsquo; run support groups. You can contact them on 0114 273 4017.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;We will be working with all our young carers groups to name and develop the content of what we&#39;re currently calling the &#39;<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/young-persons-portal\">Young Person&#39;s Portal</a>&#39;. It&#39;ll be an exciting area of the site, owned by the young carers, where they can put all the stuff they want their friends to know about from jokes and games sites to stories the young people want to tell about themselves.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Visit our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to sign up for email news for young carers.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:14:49','2010-06-17 14:14:03','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:12:00',1,34,0),(25,4,'Voluntary Sector',NULL,'<h3>\r\n	How to identify and help a young carer</h3>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Recognising some of these key signs may help you to identify young carers within children you work with:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Late for and miss days of school or social activities (such as a youth club) for no apparent reason</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Tired and withdrawn</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Difficulty joining into social and extra-curricular activities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Isolated or a victim of bullying....but in contrast they may be confident with adults</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Under-achievement in school or socially</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Secretive and protective of their home life</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Anxiety or concern for a relative and a need to be in constant contact with someone at home</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Behavioural problems, expressing pent up frustration or stress</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physical problems such as strain or injury caused by aspects of their caring role</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Positive steps that you can take to help:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Approach them in an age appropriate and sensitive way &ndash; don&rsquo;t assume that even those who outwardly appear mature and confident feel the same on the inside.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about how they feel &ndash; whilst young carers spend most of their time looking after someone at home, they may be the person who knows least about the health condition of the cared for person.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Try to encourage the cared for person to explain their health condition to the young carer; they may need your support in doing so.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Give young carers the information they need to answer questions they may have which can include &ndash; can I catch it, will it happen to me too, what caused it, was it my fault, can I do anything to make them better, will they get worse or die, what should I do in an emergency?</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Assess/consider the needs of the whole family; this is often the best way to establish and provide help for the young carer.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk to them about SYC and the services we provide, with the young carer and their parents permission you can then refer them to our service using our Talk to them about SYC and the services we provide, with the young carer and their parents permission you can then refer them to our service using our <a target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a><a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/6\" target=\"_blank\">.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are happy to support, engage with, provide information and advice to, and accept referrals from any voluntary sector organisation who become aware of / come into contact with young carers. Please use our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to get in touch.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Useful links agencies and organisations working to support young carers</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&#39;re going to be adding these as soon as we possibly can.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Keep in touch</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Visit our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to sign up for email news for professionals.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:15:02','2010-10-24 16:49:07','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:15:00',1,13,6),(27,11,'Who we are',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Sheffield Young Carers (SYC) is a registered charity (no 1066670) which has been running, supported by an active Management Committee since 1995.</h5>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:39:36','2010-06-10 14:42:16','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 10:39:36',0,39,0),(28,11,'Why we need your help',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	As a registered charity we rely 100% on charitable donations to continue and expand our work of supporting young carers in Sheffield.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Although we receive grant support towards some of our costs, every year we need more funds to meet the growing demand. We want to provide the very best support for young carers in Sheffield, who need and deserve our help.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are grateful for any support local people or businesses can offer, however small, as every penny makes a huge difference to the young people we support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Without the support of charitable donations we would cease to exist.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:40:26','2010-06-11 11:34:30','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:40:00',0,33,2),(29,11,'What you can do to help',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We are very grateful for any help that members of the public and business are able to offer to help us to continue and expand our work.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can help us in the following ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Making a one off donation &ndash; you can make a one off donation by visiting our <a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/sheffieldyoungcarers\">Just Giving</a> page online or by sending a cheque made payable to Sheffield Young Carers Project to the address on our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Becoming a regular giver &ndash; what better way to set up a regular charity donation than with a local worthwhile charity. You can do this by visiting our <a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/sheffieldyoungcarers\">Just Giving</a> page online, or by <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org/enquiries/new?id=contact\">contacting us</a> for our bank details.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Organising a fundraising event &ndash; organising something locally to raise money like a coffee morning, luncheon event, summer fete, tombola. You can also <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">contact us</a> for help and support in how to organise and promote your event.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Undertaking a sponsored event &ndash; doing an activity sponsored in aid of SYC such as a running event, swim or something more daring like a bungee jump or getting you head shaved! Again, please <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">contact us</a> for any support in organising and promoting this sponsored event. You can also set up a sponsorship page using <a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/sheffieldyoungcarers\">Just Giving</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Becoming a regular fundraiser/organiser &ndash; we are trying to get together a team of local, committed volunteers to help us organise events which raise funds for SYC. Please <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">get in touch</a> if you would be interested in helping us in this way.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Donations we receive are used for things like:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Offering young carers a free holiday/break from their caring responsibilities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Providing free of charge activity groups and excursions for young carers</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Supporting families to help reduce the responsibilities of young carers</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Training local schools and agencies to better understand young carers and support their needs</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The general running costs of the charity, things like, telephone and internet costs, postage and key staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	To find out more about major projects which we are currently raising money for please visit our <a href=\"http://www.thebiggive.org.uk/charity.php?charity_id=6896&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;search=f65aad58-3802-4adf-9b79-606bc1aea72c\">Big Give</a> web page where details are provided. You can also donate to these projects through this site.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you would like to help us but require additional information or support (such as publicity, sponsorship forms etc) please get in touch using our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page (insert link) and we will be more than happy to help.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Visit our news page to see some of the things people have done to help us recently. (insert link to news page)</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Keep in touch</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Visit our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquires/new?id=contact\">Contact Us</a> page to sign up for email news for professionals.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:40:55','2010-06-10 08:50:17','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 08:40:00',0,29,3),(30,11,'What is a young carer and how do we help them',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	A young carer is someone aged under 21 who cares for a relative or friend who has physical or mental health issues, a disability or problems with drugs or alcohol.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Young carers provide help by doing things like chores, shopping, helping with hygiene (bathing, getting dressed), giving medication and looking after younger brothers and sisters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Being a young carer can affect a young person in many ways - they aren&rsquo;t able to go out much, or able to access the same opportunities as other young people, they might end up getting in trouble for missing school or being distracted.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We aim to support young by increasing their opportunities and improving their health and well being through the offering of one to one support, group activities, respite breaksholidays and support with education, employment and training.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also work with other agencies such as schools and the health service to ensure that better support is available to young carers in their day to day life.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 10:44:10','2010-06-10 14:43:07','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 09:42:00',0,17,1),(31,12,'Young Carers 4 Life! ',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Welcome to YC4L!</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	These are pages written by young carers, for young carers - where you can find help and info about being a young carer!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you help to look after someone at home and have any ideas about things to add on these pages, or if you have any questions or need support, please contact the Young Carers Project on 0114 258 4595.</p>\r\n','2010-06-02 15:09:27','2010-10-21 21:58:24','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-02 14:09:00',1,54,0),(32,6,'Who we are',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Sheffield Young Carers is a charity set up in 1997. Our work is delivered by both paid staff and volunteers and we work with children and young people from across Sheffield aged 8-21, who are helping to care for a parent or other family member who has physical or mental health issues, a disability or substance misuse issues.</h5>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Meet our staff team</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141625_5.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=ca14607ab9158d7d\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px; \" />Liz Church &ndash; Manager</strong><br />\r\n	Liz supports all staff to make sure they provide a good service to young carers. Her job is also to work with the organisations that fund us to keep ensure the service keeps going and make links with other agencies that could help young carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_3.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=4933fc4a084c7e8a\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px; \" />Laura Selby &ndash; Support and Development Worker</strong><br />\r\n	Laura eads two social groups for young carers and does one-to-one work with young carers, when extra support is needed. She talks to other agencies to raise awareness about young carers and the issues that affect them and makes links and talks to other agencies about how they might help the young carers they work with.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141622_1.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=da3430f07ad7b2db\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px; \" />Steph Platt &ndash; Support Worker</strong><br />\r\n	Steph leads a social group for 8-12 year olds in South Sheffield.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141623_2.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=6e48b63860d28bd3\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px; \" />Denise Anderson &ndash; Administrator and Support Worker</strong><br />\r\n	Denise does the office work , including the accounts and also leads a social group for 13 - 16 year olds.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/2010/06/10/141624_4.jpg?&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;s=3f6b952affbc8894\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: left; width: 150px; height: 150px; \" />Helen Goldsby West &ndash; Fundraiser</strong><br />\r\n	Helen&#39;s main focus is researching and making applications for money to run Sheffield Young Carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Volunteers:</strong><br />\r\n	We have a great bunch of volunteers who provide amazing support to our project by volunteering at our groups or in various other roles.</p>\r\n','2010-06-10 08:03:05','2010-06-10 17:04:55','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 07:03:00',0,23,2),(33,6,'What it means to be a young carer',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	The kind of things young carers might do includes:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		House work</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Shopping</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Looking after brothers and sisters</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Personal care</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Helping them to get out of bed / move around</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Paying bills / managing finances</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Giving medication / injections</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Listening to worries and offering reassurance</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Attending appointments</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		And much more</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 08:07:50','2010-06-23 10:20:24','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 07:07:00',1,195,1),(34,6,'What we do to support young carers',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Group support</h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We run a number of groups to give young people a break from&nbsp;caring. The groups are a place for young people to socialise and have fun, as well as to meet other young people also caring for someone. The type of activities we do include:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Excursions (e.g. bowling, swimming, rock climbing)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Issue-based sessions where we explore a range of issues affecting young people who are caring (e.g. bullying, confidence, relationships or managing anger or stress)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Life-skills sessions (e.g. healthy cooking, first aid, managing finances).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Individual support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also offer one-to-one sessions to young people in our project.&nbsp; These are a chance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young people to have some time to talk about their individual situations and worries</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young people to let us know what support they want from us</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For new members to get to know a member of our staff</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young carers who are already in our groups when they need some extra support</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 08:15:53','2010-07-21 12:50:04','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 07:15:00',1,36,3),(35,6,'Want to get involved?',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	At Sheffield Young Carers, volunteers provide a great deal of support for our organisation and mean we can offer much more to young carers across Sheffield than we could on our own.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	You might like to volunteer and be involved with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Group support</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		One-to-one befriending</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Administration</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Fundraising</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Running our Management Committee.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	In practice, group support volunteers might:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Support young people and the group worker during activities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Talk and listen to young people on a one-to-one basis within the groups</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Help make the young people&rsquo;s individual experience in the group inclusive and positive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	One-to-one befrienders could be involved with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Meeting up with a young person on a regular basis (a typical commitment is between 1 - 3 hours a week)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Listening to the young person</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Offering support and leisure / social opportunities for the young person</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Please note:</strong> Volunteers must gain experience as a Group Support Volunteer within our project before we offer befriending as a volunteer opportunity</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you want to help with administraton you could:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Volunteer between half a day and one day per week</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Help with general office tasks to support the running of the project (answering phones, writing/mailing letters, word processing/typing, data entry, photocopying, writing minutes etc)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Volunteer fundraisers could:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Help fundraise for the project by planning and delivering events, placing/collecting collection boxes etc</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are always on the look out for Management Committee Members:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		People with personal or professional experience in the field of caring, health, education, social care, youth work, or fundraising/finance</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To be part of a group who steer and manage the project through bi-monthly meetings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	What you can expect from us</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Training opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Informal individual support</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Group supervision</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		All expenses paid by the project, including travel to and from the project</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Applying to be a volunteer</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	We work with children and young people so we need to be sure we get the right people as volunteers. This means, before you can volunteer at our project, you will need to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Read through the <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/2\">volunteer task description</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/5\">volunteer person specification</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Send in an <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/1\">application form</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Submit two satisfactory references</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Attend an informal interview</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Complete a CRB application form</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are interested in applying to be a volunteer, please click here . (link to application pack / email enquiry form)<br />\r\n	If you have any questions, please <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">contact us</a>. We look forward to hearing from you.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Keep in touch</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Why not sign up to receive our email news to keep in touch? You can do so <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\">here</a>.</p>\r\n','2010-06-10 08:28:50','2010-07-21 12:17:29','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 07:28:00',1,13,4),(36,4,'Who we are and what we do',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Who we are</h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Sheffield Young Carers (SYC) is a Registered Charity (no 1066670) which has been running, supported by an active Management Committee since 1995.</h5>\r\n<h2>\r\n	What we do</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We offer support to children and young people aged 8-21 who are living in Sheffield and caring for someone at home, usually a family member, with a physical or mental illness or disability or a substance misuse problem.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These children and young people are known as &lsquo;young carers&rsquo; and we aim to support them by increasing their opportunities and improving their health and well-being through the offering of one to one support, group activities, respite breaks, holidays and support with education, employment and training.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also work with our funding partners, the NHS and Sheffield City Council, and a number of other organisations, to make sure that additional support is available to young carers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We aim to challenge the exclusion that young carers face through the services and support we offer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you would like to refer a young carer to our service please use our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information about SYC and details of our staff team please visit our <a href=\"../../1\">About Us</a> page.</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Further information for supporting young carers if you work in</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/education\">Education</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/health-and-adult-social-care\">Health and Adult Social Care</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/childrens-services\">Children&rsquo;s Services</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/voluntary-sector\">Voluntary Sector</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 09:09:44','2010-10-18 08:23:36','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 08:09:00',1,41,2),(37,10,'Is my child a \'young carer\'?',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Some children help look after someone in their family by:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Staying in the house a lot to be there for them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Helping them to get up, get washed or get dressed.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Doing lots of the household chores like shopping, cleaning, cooking . . . and maybe looking after younger brothers and sisters as well</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	For many families, this seems like the only option &ndash; you may be a single parent family with no relatives living nearby, or a two parent family but one of you works long hours.</p>\r\n','2010-06-10 12:34:55','2010-06-17 14:10:00','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 12:34:55',1,52,0),(38,10,'How we support young carers',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Group Support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We run a number of groups to give young people a break from their caring role. The groups are a place for young people to socialise and have fun, as well as to meet other young people who are also caring for someone. The type of activities we do include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Excursions (e.g. bowling, swimming, rock climbing)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Issue-based sessions where we explore things affect young people who are caring (e.g. bullying, confidence, relationships or managing anger or stress)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Life-skills sessions (e.g. healthy cooking, first aid, managing finances).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Individual Support</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also offer one-to-one sessions to young people in our project. The one-to-one sessions are a chance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young people to have some time to talk about their individual situations and worries</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young people to let us know what support they want from us</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For new members to get to know a member of our staff</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For young carers who are already in our groups when they need some extra support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 12:36:58','2010-10-21 22:11:57','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 12:36:58',1,14,0),(41,10,'How we could support you',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We may be able to offer some support to the child who is taking on a caring role. This may make you feel easier knowing they have a place to go with other young people in a similar situation.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is the family&#39;s choice whether you would like to receive support from Sheffield Young Carers. We only accept referrals where the young carer has given permission to share information with us. We also ask for the parent/carer&#39;s consent wherever possible.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Families can refer themselves over the <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/enquiries/new?id=contact\" target=\"_blank\">phone</a> or by requesting a home visit from one of our workers to complete the referral form.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We could also put you in contact with other agencies who may be able to offer services and support for your needs e.g. practical, emotional, etc<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2010-06-10 12:40:18','2010-10-21 22:13:23','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 12:40:18',1,27,0),(43,10,'Useful links',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Here&#39;s some external sources of information which you might like to look at to find other support:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For information about getting help for you or for the person who is caring for someone, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarers.net/parents\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For easy-to-understand information about a different health issues, click <a href=\"http://www.childrenfirst.nhs.uk/\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For links to support around health, legal advice and finding someone to talk to, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarer.com/showPage.php?file=families.htm\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you are worried about someone&rsquo;s feelings and mental health, <a href=\"http://www.youngminds.org.uk\">see</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you want to find about all the different activities and support for children and young people in Sheffield, <a href=\"http://www.asksid.net\">click here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend is living with someone misusing drugs or alcohol, they can get support from the &lsquo;What About Me&rsquo; project by phoning 0114 275 5973.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend is affected by HIV/AIDS, they can get support from the &lsquo;Sheena Amos Youth Trust&rsquo; by phoning 0114 281 1352.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend has a brother or sister with a disability, there is help available from &lsquo;Sibling Support&rsquo; on 0114 273 4017</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you are an adult caring for someone, you can get information <a href=\"http://www.carersinformation.org.uk\">from</a>. You can also get support through local groups through the <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldcarers.org.uk/\">Sheffield Carers Centre</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 13:28:42','2010-06-17 14:13:19','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 13:28:42',1,49,0),(44,8,'Useful links',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Here&#39;s some external sources of information which you might like to look at to find other support:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For information about getting help for you or for the person who is caring for someone, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarers.net/parents\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For easy-to-understand information about different health issues, click <a href=\"http://www.childrenfirst.nhs.uk/\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		For links to support around health, legal advice and finding someone to talk to, click <a href=\"http://www.youngcarer.com/showPage.php?file=families.htm\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you are worried about someone&rsquo;s feelings and mental health, click <a href=\"http://www.youngminds.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you want to find about all the different activities and support for children and young people in Sheffield, click<a href=\"http://www.asksid.net/\"> here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend is living with someone misusing drugs or alcohol, they can get support from the &lsquo;What About Me&rsquo; project by phoning 0114 275 5973.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend is affected by HIV/AIDS, they can get support from the &lsquo;Sheena Amos Youth Trust&rsquo; by phoning 0114 281 1352.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If your child or friend has a brother or sister with a disability, there is help available from &lsquo;Sibling Support&rsquo; on 0114 273 4017</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		If you are an adult caring for someone, you can get information from <a href=\"http://www.carersinformation.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. You can also get support through local groups through the <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldcarers.org.uk/\">Sheffield Carers Centre</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-10 13:29:13','2010-10-21 22:10:51','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-10 13:29:13',1,50,0),(45,14,'Legal',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Sheffield Young Carers Project</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sheaf Bank Business Park<br />\r\n	Unit R7b, Riverside Block<br />\r\n	20 Prospect Road<br />\r\n	Sheffield<br />\r\n	S2 3EN</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tel: 0114 258 4595<br />\r\n	Email: <a href=\"mailto:information@sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk\"> information@sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Registered charity no. 1066670<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2010-06-11 08:27:24','2010-06-11 08:28:17','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-11 08:27:24',0,NULL,0),(46,14,'Website credits',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Sheffield Young Carers is grateful to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\">Yoomee</a> for designing and building such a fantastic new site</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.nigelbarkerphotography.co.uk/\">Nigel Barker</a> for taking such stunning photos</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		All the young carers and friends of Sheffield Young Carers whose photos appear on the site - you look awesome</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2010-06-11 08:31:55','2010-06-11 08:31:55','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-06-11 08:31:55',0,NULL,0),(50,2,'Kind Donations to SYC – Many thanks!',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We would like to express our thanks to local people who have been kind enough to make recent donations to the important work of our charity.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Mr and Mrs Ashburner of Sheffield made the kind decision to ask guests to their wedding to donate funds to our charity instead of buying gifts. This amazingly selfless gesture has raised <strong>&pound;437.50</strong> (including Gift Aid) for which we are VERY grateful. <strong>Thank you Ashburners and all the best for the future</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We have just had word that the kind shoppers of Waitrose Sheffield have enabled us to raise an astounding <strong>&pound;490 </strong>through the Waitrose Community Matters token scheme &ndash; so <strong>thank you local shoppers and also Waitrose staff!</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	All donations however small make a huge difference to our charity and in turn the young carers of Sheffield so <strong>please keep giving.</strong></p>\r\n','2010-07-07 11:01:09','2010-10-13 21:23:10','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-07-07 09:01:00',1,296,5),(52,2,'New members in the SYC team',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	In August and September, SYC welcomed two new members to our team.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Seetal Jassal started working with us in August and is our new Young People&#39;s Worker, running five of our young people&#39;s groups, as well as offering lots of one-to-one support sessions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	From the end of September, SYC also welcomed Julian Ainsley to the project. Julian is a trainee Social Worker from Sheffield Hallam University on placement with us until the end of January 2011 and will be getting involved with all areas of our work.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>A big welcome to Seetal and Julian!</strong></p>\r\n','2010-07-21 12:29:47','2010-11-04 15:25:37','2010-11-12 11:29:00','2010-10-13 10:29:00',1,300,2),(53,2,'Young Carers Granted £4000 to Spread the Word',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	During July, nine SYC project members, all aged between 12-16, got together to write a funding bid to the Youth Opportunity Fund. After being successfully shortlisted, six young people attended Sheffield Town Hall to present why they want the funding in front of a room full of young people and adults.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Gaby, Beckie and Shannon gave a great presentation, cheered on by Daniel, Curtis and Taymar, and they were successfully granted <strong>&pound;4000</strong>. They will use this set up a participation group to have more of a say about what happens for young carers in Sheffield, as well as to do awareness-raising training about young carers in schools and other settings around the city. This will help people understand how to support young carers better and help young carers who are caring alone to get some help and support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Well done to everyone involved! And watch this space for updates on the project....</strong></p>\r\n','2010-07-22 11:56:59','2010-10-13 21:05:14','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-07-22 11:36:00',1,359,4),(54,15,'Jessica\'s Story',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	My name is Jessica and I am 13 years old. Four years ago my mum fell ill with fibromyalgia, diverticulitis and joint problems. This means she can&#39;t go out of the house and she is in alot of pain when she moves. At first she was alright but it got worse.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	I started looking after my 2 younger sisters aged 2 and 4. My dad helped but was at work from 6am till 10pm and was tired when he got home. I cleaned, cooked and looked after my sisters. It got worse when I started high school. I had so much homework and was so stressed. Also my dad left so the stress kept building up. I missed a lot of school as well because I was ill from stress.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	My mum hated relying on me so she found out about Young Carers and contacted them through her support worker. I started going to their Monday group and it helped me cope a lot. I got to make new friends and go out on trips. The stress became less as I learned to cope with it and started getting help. I can ring my mum at school now so I don&rsquo;t worry about her so much and I can always tell the Young Carers leaders about my problems.</p>\r\n','2010-07-27 14:24:48','2010-10-24 15:29:34','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-07-27 14:24:48',1,225,0),(55,15,'Shannon\'s Story',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	I am 14 and I care for my mum. After some bad things that happened in her life, my mum has suffered with severe anxiety and depression and also has agoraphobia. This means she&rsquo;s too scared to leave the house and feels very down and worried about things. She has also been in hospital twice and her illness affects her mentally and physically.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	I have to go to the shops, make cups of tea, wash the pots and other stuff like help her to look after my little brother and sister. It affects me emotionally and mentally knowing that she just wants to live a normal life and do normal stuff like take us out on holiday or on fun days out and because she can&rsquo;t it makes her feel like she&rsquo;s useless. But she&rsquo;s not, she&rsquo;s my world, without her I would be heart broken. She&rsquo;s so strong at keeping her emotions in but sometimes she has breakdowns, so I&rsquo;m always there to support her and I always will be, no matter what.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I find it hard at school because I always want to be with her when she needs me but I can&rsquo;t always be. I also often cry at school. The school know about my mum so they let me go to LSU (learner support unit) where I can relax and not worry and talk to someone.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	When I come to Young Carers I don&rsquo;t have to worry and its helps a lot. My mum wants me to have some kind of childhood and meet others so she likes me coming to the group. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	So, if you&rsquo;re like me and you&rsquo;re looking after someone in your family, you should come to Young Carers and speak to someone about it. Without Young Carers I would feel much more alone!</p>\r\n','2010-07-27 14:43:45','2010-10-24 15:37:29','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-07-27 14:43:45',1,195,0),(56,2,'Thank you Waitrose Customers',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<strong>SYC would like to give a big thank you to customers of Waitrose who supported our project with their charity tokens during the month of June.</strong></h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	We received &pound;490 thanks to the kind donations of customers at the Ecclesall Road branch of the store. This will go a really long way to providing more well-needed support and breaks for young carers across Sheffield. The cheque was collected by two of our project members who were also given some delicious goodies courtesy of Waitrose. Everyone at the project is very grateful for this support - once again, THANK YOU!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you would like to make a donation to our project, please click <a href=\"../../../what-you-can-do-to-help\">here.</a></p>\r\n','2010-08-12 14:25:57','2010-10-13 21:04:40','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-08-12 14:04:00',1,360,5),(57,12,'What we do at Young Carers',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	At Young Carers we do loads of different things to help us.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes we go out as a treat or other times we talk about what we do at home for the person we look after. Today we have been to a group to decide what should be on this website. We also do games and sports outside and loads of other actvities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>By TB, young carer age 12</em></p>\r\n','2010-08-12 14:33:45','2010-08-12 14:34:47','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-08-12 14:33:45',1,290,0),(58,2,'Sheffield Young Carers live on stage',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Since the summer, SYC members have been working with Point Blank Theatre to develop their own moving and thought-provoking performance and film to show what it&#39;s really like being a young carer.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	They performed the play, called &#39;A Life in a Day&#39;, during October half term to two public audiences, who were amazed by their skills,&nbsp;honesty and confidence. Comments after the show included &#39;exceptional&#39;, &#39;confident&#39; and &#39;fantastic performance&#39; and many of those who attended were so moved by the performance they have vowed to take action to improve support and services for young carers in Sheffield. An amazing acheivement - well done to everyone involved!!!</p>\r\n','2010-10-13 21:18:56','2010-11-09 15:45:13','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-10-13 21:12:00',1,361,1),(59,2,'Young Carers Taking on the World',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	After talking about how hard school can be for young carers, SYC members decided to raise the profile of young carers in schools in Sheffield, so other young carers out there can get better support.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	A group of members aged 13-16 have volunteered to go out and speak in school assemblies so students and staff understand a bit more. They are also working with members of Sheffield UK Youth Parliament to develop a Young Carers ID card that could be given out by schools.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The first assemblies are happening in early November and we hope to take this to all schools in Sheffield...and maybe the world!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you would like an assembly or workshop about young carers and the issues they face, please get in touch with Laura, SYC&#39;s Development Worker.</p>\r\n','2010-10-13 21:33:21','2010-10-13 21:39:42','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-10-13 21:23:00',1,160,2),(60,4,'Making a referral',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	SYC offers support to children and young people aged 8-21 who are living in Sheffield and caring for someone at home, usually a family member, with physical or mental illness, a disability, and/or a substance misuse problem.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are working with a young person who is in a caring role, please discuss our project with them and their family. If they would like our support, please complete our <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/7\" target=\"_blank\">Referral Form</a> with them and send it in to us.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This will then be dicussed at our weekly team meeting and an allocated worker will get back to you. If we are the right people to offer support, we will then arrange a joint visit with you to meet the young person and, where possible, the cared-for person to talk through the support we can offer them.</p>\r\n','2010-10-18 08:27:00','2010-10-24 16:51:03','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-10-18 08:27:00',1,95,6),(61,15,'Ashley\'s Story',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	I am 11 and I care for my dad. He has no kidneys. He&#39;s had two transplants but both of them failed so he&#39;s waiting for another. But he&#39;s got a heart problem as well so he&#39;s got to get that fixed first.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes I get really worried about my dad, like now when he&#39;s waiting for a big operation, because I don&#39;t know what&#39;s going to happen and how things are going to go. A good thing though is the quality time I get with my dad - I&#39;ve got a really close bond with him because we&#39;re together so much.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Its different being a young carer because other young people get to do what they want. But when you&#39;ve got someone with an illness in your family, you don&#39;t have a choice. You don&#39;t get as much time as other people have. Its not that easy for people who have to care for someone.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since I joined Sheffield Young Carers, its helped me because I get to do groups so I can have a little break from caring. Its fun. They also give me support that I wouldn&rsquo;t get from other people because they know how it is to have someone in your family who&#39;s poorly or got something wrong with them. I know I can talk to them even if I can&#39;t talk to anyone else.</p>\r\n','2010-10-24 15:13:17','2010-10-24 15:32:02','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-10-24 15:13:17',1,284,0),(62,15,'Eden\'s Story',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	I am 10 and I care for my mum who has bi-polar depression and fibromyalgia.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sometimes my mum&#39;s in a lot of pain and can&#39;t move. Also, she can be very happy but she can be very sad. When she&#39;s happy, she&#39;s really happy and nice and that makes me happy. But when she&#39;s sad, she&#39;s really sad and just wants to burst into tears every day. And that makes me sad, even though I know its not her fault.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I joined Sheffield Young Carers a few months ago and I like it because it takes off that big responsibility for a few hours. I get to go to a group where we play and do arts and crafts and things. This summer, we also went on lots of trips and a residential for 3 days where we did raft building and lots of other fun things. It was wacky!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I also get to talk to someone one-to-one which gives me a chance to speak about my feelings.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I&#39;m really glad I joined Young Carers!</p>','2010-10-24 15:25:00','2010-10-24 15:29:50','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-10-24 15:25:00',1,34,0),(64,2,'SYC Job Vacancies',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We currently have two vacancies at Sheffield Young Carers. Please click the vacancy you are interested in for details.&nbsp;</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/24\" target=\"_blank\">Young Carers Family Worker </a>(full time)</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.sheffieldyoungcarers.org.uk/documents/23\" target=\"_blank\">Fundraiser Officer </a>(part time)</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	The closing date for both vacancies is <strong>Wednesday 1st December 2010.</strong></p>\r\n','2010-11-04 15:13:58','2010-11-09 14:01:02','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2010-11-04 15:13:00',1,358,0);
